      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Invasive vines are no doubt blanketing Westchester's trees (''Vines Threaten Trees Along Highways,'' Sept. 17). Also affecting the scenic landscape recently has been the aggressive growth of concrete sound barricades.</p>
        <p>Perhaps as we cut away the vines, consideration should be given to planting a minimally invasive vine variety along these unsightly concrete walls. The beautiful carpet of ivy created will help absorb sound while making the walls disappear under a blanket of green.</p>
        <p>DR. SETH L. NEUBARDT  Rye</p>
      </block>
